posts.raw_content:
Well I had a bit of a scare Tuesday night and ended up in the emergency room. 

I awoke this past Sunday with a bad headache. All through Sunday, Monday, and Tuesday I was taking aspirin/acetaminophen to keep it at bay, with so-so results.

Then Tuesday night, just before bedtime my head felt like it was going to explode. It was like no headache I’ve ever had before and it’s the worst pain I’ve ever felt. 

My wife checked my blood pressure and it was 205/100. Now, I don’t like going to the Dr. or to hospitals, but I know that a bp that high is a legitimate 911 emergency. So off to the hospital we went. 

I found out that when you present with bp that high, there’s no waiting to be seen by the er staff. I was taken straight back. 

They checked my bp again and it was 200/98. They popped an IV into me and gave me several drugs in it that I don’t recall the names of (other than benedril, I remember that one) then they did an EKG and a CAT scan. 

One of the drugs they gave me hit pretty hard and I started shaking like I was convulsing. That scared the crap out of everyone and the staff kept asking me questions like my name, my date of birth, etc (to make sure I wasn’t having a stroke, I imagine). 

The EKG and the CAT scan came back looking good, so I just had to stay there and suck down IV bags of saline, waiting for my bp to lower to a safe level. After a couple of hours I went back home. 

The doctors believe that this was an episode, not a chronic condition. I’m now on a mild bp medicine that I can quit taking once my bp goes back to normal (it’s still a bit high), and the headache goes away. 

Whew! That was not fun at all. I do not recommend and I award the experience 0 out of 5 stars. 

Seriously, get yourself a bp cuff and check it now and then. Don’t mess around with high blood pressure. It’s something that needs to be addressed asap.

Please pray for my speedy recovery.
